From: "Amit Mahajan" <amahajan@aptaracorp.com> To: "'Pawan Sharma'" <pawan.sharma1@aptaracorp.com> Cc: "'Ashok kumar'" <Ashok.kumar@aptaracorp.com>, <mohd.nadeem@aptaracorp.com>, "'ppgprocess-tech'" <ppgprocess-tech@aptaracorp.com> Date: Thu, 23 Oct 2025 11:11:02 +0530 Subject: RE: A Text and XML (eMFC/1T/2T) feedback is added [22058] Hi Pawan, Below checks are not for S5. It’s for S100, Proof and S200: Please add the validation if [] coming at the start of footnote. <ce:note-para id="notep0001"><ce:sup>[]</ce:sup> Eu Please add the validation if text “et ” is coming in <sb:comment>et</sb:comment> tag. Thanks Amit From: Sanjay Kumar Pandey [mailto:sanjay.pandey1@aptaracorp.com] Sent: 22 October 2025 09:45 To: Arun.sharma@aptaracorp.com Cc: 'Amit Mahajan'; 'Ashok kumar'; 'Nidhi Gusain' Subject: RE: A Text and XML (eMFC/1T/2T) feedback is added [22058] Dear Sharma Ji, Investigation: As per our investigation, square brackets were present around footnote labels in source file (i.e. [3]). During XML conversion, these the labels are shifted to beginning of footnote text and brackets remains as is []. Example: <ce:cross-ref id="crf0005" refid="cit_1"><ce:sup>1</ce:sup></ce:cross-ref><ce:footnote id="cit_1"><ce:label>1</ce:label><ce:note-para id="notep0001"><ce:sup>[]</ce:sup> European Commission, A European strategy for data, 2020; German Federal Government, Datenstrategie der Bundesregierung, 2023.</ce:note-para></ce:footnote> Thanks and regards Sanjay Pandey From: Sanjay Kumar Pandey [mailto:sanjay.pandey1@aptaracorp.com] Sent: 17 October 2025 11:25 To: 'Amit Mahajan'; 'Ashok kumar' Cc: 'Arun sharma' Subject: FW: A Text and XML (eMFC/1T/2T) feedback is added [22058] Hi Amit Sir, As per our analysis, presence of [ ] around footnote labels in source file caused this error. Please review this and suggest if this is pre-editor’s error. Can we ask vendor team to analyse this. Ashok sir, please check from copyediting point of view. Regards Sanjay Pandey From: Arun sharma [mailto:arun.sharma@aptaracorp.com] Sent: 17 October 2025 09:28 To: 'Sanjay Kumar Pandey' Subject: FW: A Text and XML (eMFC/1T/2T) feedback is added [22058] From: svc-scielsUFF <svc-scielsUFF@elsevier.com> Sent: 16 October 2025 13:58 To: n.murugesan@elsevier.com; gsm-sqm@elsevier.com; Aptara_UF@aptaracorp.com Cc: r.luiz@elsevier.com Subject: A Text and XML (eMFC/1T/2T) feedback is added [22058] CAUTION: This email originated from outside of the organization. Do not click links or open attachments unless you recognize the sender and know the content is safe. Hi, Please find below the Text and XML (eMFC/1T/2T) upstream feedback report: E L S E V I E R Text and XML (eMFC/1T/2T) Upstream Feedback Aptara Corp.
